
CLINICFLOWAC QUICK START GUIDE

═══════════════════════════════════════

WHAT YOU'LL DO IN 5 MINUTES:

1. Clone repository
2. Install dependencies
3. Run locally
4. Test health endpoint
5. Deploy options

═══════════════════════════════════════

STEP 1: CLONE REPOSITORY

$ git clone https://github.com/aydncy/clinicflowac-oss.git
$ cd clinicflowac-oss

Time: 1 minute

═══════════════════════════════════════

STEP 2: INSTALL DEPENDENCIES

$ dart pub get

Requirements:
- Dart 3.0+ (included with Flutter SDK)
- Git

Time: 2 minutes

═══════════════════════════════════════

STEP 3: RUN LOCALLY

$ dart run bin/server.dart

Output should show:
✅ ClinicFlowAC Backend starting...
✅ ClinicFlowAC running at http://localhost:8080

Time: 1 minute

═══════════════════════════════════════

STEP 4: TEST IT

$ curl http://localhost:8080/health

Response:
{"status":"healthy","service":"ClinicFlowAC","version":"1.0.0"}

═══════════════════════════════════════

STEP 5: NEXT OPTIONS

Option A: Local Testing
- Run locally for development
- Perfect for learning

Option B: Deploy to Cloud (FREE)
- Render.com: https://render.com
- Railway.app: https://railway.app
- Takes 5 minutes

Option C: Deploy to VPS ($5/month)
- DigitalOcean: https://digitalocean.com
- Linode: https://linode.com
- AWS: https://aws.amazon.com

═══════════════════════════════════════

